Disk Forensics > [T9]: AmCache.hve: Tracking Installed Programs and History

(6) AmCache.hve Registry Hive

The AmCache.hve file (also known as the "Windows File Protection Cache") is used by the Windows operating system to store information about the files that are installed on a system. This file is located in the "C:\Windows\AppCompat\Programs" directory and can be used to track the history of installed programs and updates.

The AmCache.hve file can be useful for forensic investigators because it contains a record of all the files that have been installed on a system, including the name, version, and location of each file. This information can be used to identify the programs installed on a system and determine when they were installed.

It is worth noting that the AmCache.hve file is a binary file and cannot be directly viewed or edited. You will need to use a specialized tool to access the information it contains or convert the file to a more readable format.

 The AmCache.hve file is located at "C:\Windows\appcompat\Programs\Amcache.hve".

Using the "AmcacheParser" tool to parse the AmCache.hve file will generate several CSV files. One of the most useful files is the "UnassociatedFileEntries," which contains a list of installed applications. By examining this list, you can identify any suspicious entries and look up their SHA1 hashes to see if they are known malicious executables. You can also use this information to create a unique blacklist or whitelist for your organization.
